tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement for their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned key UI components, and updated styling across all sections to
  create a more calming and professional user experience.
overview: "The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app's
  aesthetics from a generic look to a more beautiful and calming experience. I
  started by analyzing the existing design, identifying issues like a generic
  color palette and plain components. The approach involved a comprehensive
  update: introducing a sophisticated sleep-themed color palette, redesigning
  the main form layout with subtle decorative elements, enhancing the intro
  section with engaging feature cards, and polishing all interactive form
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. A key decision was to
  standardize the visual grouping of questions across all sections, replacing
  old gray boxes with new card-style elements. The outcome is a significantly
  improved, professional, and visually consistent application that better
  reflects a sleep health assessment."
